Text: U-Um... Lady Karen!
You've strayed quite far from your home...!
I prefer a wider venue when stamping out pests.
Pests... Oh!
Grrr, a strange band...and even Velgaltan soldiers?!

It would seem we've passed the point of keeping up
appearances... But!
Don't think you can best me so easily!
(No sign of Sergey or the Children...)

(Do they think Annerose's accusations aren't
worth their time?)

(Were they wanting to avoid a run-in with the
Templars like Lady Zeta intended? Or maybe
there's some other reason at play?)
Either way, your lives end here!

...Annerose and No. 111 have engaged Sergey's
minions.

Sergey himself is not present, and as before, no
powerful forces such as the Children have been
deployed.
I see...

It really is odd that even now the Cult hasn't made
an earnest effort to eliminate Annerose.
What do you make of all this, No. 122?

Well...it's true that, as we hypothesized, Sergey and
his forces shied away from a real confrontation with
the Templars. However—

in my personal view, this could signify a lack of
trust between the Rounds in the Cult of Diablos
and Sergey, neophyte that he is.

This state of affairs is by no means them taking
Annerose lightly. Rather, it may be the result of
them being unable to act effectively as an
organization here.

Could be there was some reason they never felt the
situation was a big deal to begin with. Not to
mention that Sergey snubbed the Fenrir sect's offer
of an alliance.

Maybe he's a political dunce of a firebrand, maybe
he's playing some other game...

And if the majority of the factions in the Cult are
hoping to remove Sergey, that would explain why
they've turned somewhat of a blind eye toward this
incident.

...Either way, we don't have to worry about No.111.
I'm going to turn my attention to our Templar friends.

Will you be alright on your own? With No. 111 safe,
I could join you—

For various reasons, it's better if I handle them
alone.
Various...reasons?

Yeah, various reasons. Now continue to look after
No. 111.
Understood. Please be careful on your end as well.
Where am I...?

A storage space formerly used by the gardener of
Herzog Manor.

Since a new storehouse was built attached to the
residence itself for security reasons, this place has
fallen into a state of neglect, as you can see—

...That floorboard there can be removed without any
tools.
This one...here?

Yes, that is the one, Annerose... Now, move that
floorboard!
It came off. I see a box beneath—

You will find various documents hidden inside. I've
been gathering them in secret since Sergey murdered
my family.
*gasp*
Lady Karen, you...

You sensed that your life was in danger and hid the
evidence here in preparation for the worst!

I was unable to level charges against Sergey...but
this will be vital proof in demonstrating his crimes.

I entrust my honor as a knight of Velgalta, and as
one of the Seven Blades...to you.

Very well... Then I, Annerose Nichtsehen, swear upon
this knight's blade, to avenge you and your kin!
